        <article class="content-block">
          <h2>Contact</h2>
          <p>GitHub Issues are the primary support route for reproducible bugs because they make investigation easier to track. For questions, feature ideas, or setup discussion, use GitHub Discussions.</p>
          <p class="button-row"><a class="button primary" href="https://github.com/eslutz/PumpSync/issues/new/choose" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Open a GitHub Issue</a> <a class="button" href="https://github.com/eslutz/PumpSync/discussions" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub Discussions</a></p>
          <p>Email is available at <a href="mailto:support@ericslutz.dev?subject=PUMPSYNC%20SUPPORT">support@ericslutz.dev</a>. Keep the subject prefix <strong>PUMPSYNC SUPPORT</strong> so support mail is routed correctly.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="content-block">
          <h2>Before reporting a bug</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Include the app version, iOS version, device model, and whether you are using PumpSync Hosted or a self-hosted backend.</li>
            <li>Describe the step that failed: subscription restore, backend session, Tandem credential validation, Tandem sync, or Apple Health write.</li>
            <li>Include the backend URL only for self-hosted installations where sharing it is safe.</li>
            <li>Do not include Tandem passwords, service tokens, App Store receipts, screenshots with health data, or other sensitive medical details.</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="content-block">
          <h2>FAQ</h2>
          <div class="faq">
            <h3>What does PumpSync do?</h3>
            <p>PumpSync syncs Tandem Source pump data to Apple Health at the user's request, including insulin and carbohydrate samples when supported by the current sync flow.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq">
            <h3>Do I need PumpSync Hosted?</h3>
            <p>No. PumpSync supports a hosted subscription path and a self-hosted path where you point the app at a backend you operate.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq">
            <h3>Where are Tandem credentials stored?</h3>
            <p>The iOS app stores Tandem credentials in the device Keychain with device-only accessibility. Credentials are sent to the backend only during an active HTTPS sync request.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq">
            <h3>Does PumpSync keep my Tandem health data on the backend?</h3>
            <p>No. The backend does not persist Tandem credentials, Tandem tokens, raw Tandem events, or normalized Tandem samples.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq">
            <h3>How do I remove data?</h3>
            <p>See the <a href="/privacy/data-deletion/">data deletion page</a> for Tandem credential removal, Apple Health access revocation, hosted metadata deletion, and self-hosted deletion guidance.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq">
            <h3>Is PumpSync medical advice?</h3>
            <p>No. PumpSync is not a medical device and does not provide medical advice, diagnosis, treatment, or dosing recommendations.</p>
          </div>
        </article>
